### Step 12 — Modify `src/app/story/[id]/page.tsx`

Additions to state/hooks section:

```typescript
const [isHistoryOpen, setIsHistoryOpen] = useState(false);
const [restoreConfirmation, setRestoreConfirmation] = useState<string | null>(null);
```

Wire `useVersionHistory`:
```typescript
const {
  versions,
  hasVersions,
  saveNamedDraft,
  restoreToVersion,
  refreshVersions,
} = useVersionHistory({
  storyId: id,
  content,
  onRestore: (restoredContent, entry) => {
    setContent(restoredContent);     // triggers autosave debounce + snapshot
    setIsHistoryOpen(false);
    setRestoreConfirmation(`Restored to version from ${formatRelativeTime(entry.timestamp)}`);
    setTimeout(() => setRestoreConfirmation(null), 4000);
  },
});
```

Note: `setContent` is from `useAutosave`. Calling it with the restored content is the correct path — it writes the crash-recovery snapshot and queues the debounced autosave, so the restored content is persisted even if the user closes the tab immediately.

Import `formatRelativeTime` from `@/lib/autosave` (already partially imported in the file via the `clearSnapshot` import; add to that import line).

History button in `editorHeader` (add after `<SaveStatus>`):
```tsx
{hasVersions && (
  <button
    type="button"
    className={isHistoryOpen ? styles.historyButtonActive : styles.historyButton}
    onClick={() => { setIsHistoryOpen(true); refreshVersions(); }}
    aria-label="Open draft history"
    aria-expanded={isHistoryOpen}
  >
    {/* clock SVG icon */} History
  </button>
)}
```

Restore confirmation toast (add inside `editorCanvas`, below existing banners):
```tsx
{restoreConfirmation && (
  <div
    className={styles.bannerContainer}
    role="status"
    aria-live="polite"
  >
    <p className={styles.restoreConfirmationToast}>{restoreConfirmation}</p>
  </div>
)}
```

Overlay + panel (render outside `editorLayout` but inside the outer `page` div, so it covers the editor):
```tsx
{isHistoryOpen && (
  <div className={styles.historyOverlay}>
    <VersionHistory
      versions={versions}
      onRestore={restoreToVersion}
      onSaveNamedDraft={saveNamedDraft}
      onClose={() => setIsHistoryOpen(false)}
    />
  </div>
)}
```

The overlay click-outside handler: add `onClick={() => setIsHistoryOpen(false)}` on the `.historyOverlay` div; stop propagation inside `VersionHistory` panel's aside element with `onClick={(e) => e.stopPropagation()}`.

