Note on "editor dims to opacity: 0.5": the overlay backdrop at `rgba(0,0,0,0.2)` covers the editor area. Do not set `opacity: 0.5` on the editor element itself — that would affect the panel rendering too since it is rendered inside the overlay. The semi-transparent backdrop achieves the same visual result without the CSS stacking context problem.

Also note the `editorHeader` currently has no `display: flex` — review the existing CSS. The header uses `padding` only; the title input takes `width: 100%`. The History button needs `margin-left: auto` only if the header is flex. Check: the header does not currently declare `display: flex`. To position the button to the right of SaveStatus without disrupting existing layout, add `display: flex; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--spacing-sm);` to `.editorHeader`. The title input will need `flex: 1 1 100%` or the existing `width: 100%` handling will require an adjustment. Safest approach: add `display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; gap: var(--spacing-sm);` to `.editorHeader` and set `.editorHeader .titleInput { flex: 1 1 100%; }` to maintain full-width title on its own row, with ViewModeSwitch and SaveStatus + History button on a second row.

