## Test plan

### 1. Auto-checkpoint fires

- Open a story, type content, wait idle 5 minutes.
- Open History panel — exactly 1 "Auto-checkpoint" entry appears with correct word count and relative timestamp.
- Edit content again (different text), wait another 5 minutes — 2 entries appear.
- Confirm: if content has NOT changed since last checkpoint, no duplicate entry is added.

### 2. Auto-checkpoint does not fire for empty content

- Load editor with no content, wait 5 minutes — History button does not appear (0 versions, `hasVersions` is false).

### 3. Retention cap

- Write a script or mock localStorage to pre-populate 52 auto-checkpoint entries for a story.
- Trigger one more auto-checkpoint — assert only 50 auto entries remain (oldest 2 dropped) and all named drafts still present.

### 4. Named draft save

- Open History panel, type a label into "Name this draft" input, click "Save draft".
- Panel refreshes: new entry appears at the top of the list with the label in bold.
- Named entry survives the retention cap test (never dropped).

### 5. Preview flow

- Click "Preview" on any version entry.
- Preview pane opens with read-only textarea containing the version's full text.
- "Back to history" returns to the list.

### 6. Restore from list

- Click "Restore" on a version in the list.
- Editor content updates to the version content.
- History panel closes.
- Confirmation toast appears: "Restored to version from Xm ago" auto-dismisses after 4 seconds.
- A new "Auto-checkpoint" entry (the pre-restore safety snapshot) now appears at the top of the history.
- Open localStorage in DevTools: `story_{id}_snapshot` contains the content that was in the editor before restore.

### 7. Restore from preview

- Navigate to preview pane, click "Restore from this version".
- Same assertions as step 6.

### 8. History button visibility

- Brand new story with no content: History button is absent.
- After first auto-checkpoint: History button appears.

### 9. Click-outside closes panel

- Open History panel, click on the dimmed editor area — panel closes.

### 10. Escape key closes panel

- Open History panel, press Escape — panel closes.

### 11. Focus management

- Open History panel: close button receives focus.
- Close panel: focus returns to History button in header (add `historyButtonRef` in page.tsx, call `.focus()` in `onClose` handler).

### 12. Accessibility audit

- Screen reader: panel has `aria-label="Draft History"`, version entries have unique `aria-label` for Preview and Restore buttons.
- History button has `aria-expanded` reflecting open/closed state.
- Restore confirmation is announced via `role="status"` and `aria-live="polite"`.

### 13. localStorage edge case — storage full

- Mock `localStorage.setItem` to throw a `QuotaExceededError`.
- Confirm: auto-checkpoint failure is silently caught (does not break editing); named draft save also silently fails without crashing.

