## Risks and mitigations

| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|
| `setInterval` in `useVersionHistory` reads stale content if not guarded with `useRef` | High (happened in BIN-64) | `contentRef.current = content` in render body, timer reads `contentRef.current` — not state |
| localStorage quota exceeded when storing many large stories with version history | Medium | `enforceRetention` limits auto entries to 50; `saveVersions` swallows QuotaExceeded silently so editing continues |
| Restore replaces content without safety snapshot if `restoreVersion` in lib fails midway | Low | Safety snapshot (`saveSnapshot`) is the first operation in `restoreVersion`, before any array mutation |
| Panel overlay prevents editing while open but user expects panel to be closable by keyboard | Low | Escape key handler in `VersionHistory.tsx` + click-outside on overlay div |
| `margin-left: auto` on History button may not work if `.editorHeader` lacks `display: flex` | Medium | Step 13 explicitly adds `display: flex` to `.editorHeader`; noted as required change |
| Named draft input submits empty label if user clicks "Save draft" without typing | Low | Guard `label.trim() !== ''` before calling `addNamedVersion` in both hook and component |
| Page renders "History" button during SSR causing hydration mismatch if `getVersions` returns different lengths server vs. client | Low | `getVersions` returns `[]` when `typeof window === 'undefined'` (same pattern as `loadContent` in `autosave.ts`); `hasVersions` will be `false` on server and client initial render, then update in a `useEffect` if needed |

---

## Rollback strategy

All new code is additive. The two modified files (`page.tsx`, `page.module.css`) add new state and UI that can be reverted independently.

To roll back:
1. Remove the `useVersionHistory` hook call and all related state from `page.tsx`.
2. Remove the History button and overlay JSX from `page.tsx`.
3. Remove the CSS additions from `page.module.css`.
4. The new files (`versions.ts`, `useVersionHistory.ts`, `VersionHistory/` directory) can remain dead code until deleted — they import nothing from the page layer so they cannot cause regressions.
5. The `story_{storyId}_versions` localStorage key is harmless orphan data if the feature is disabled; it can be cleared manually or with a one-time migration script.

---

## Observability

Add `console.log` calls (matching the existing pattern in `autosave.ts` and `stories.ts`) at:

- `addAutoCheckpoint`: `console.log(\`Auto-checkpoint saved for story ${storyId} (total: ${versions.length})\`)`
- `addNamedVersion`: `console.log(\`Named draft '${label}' saved for story ${storyId}\`)`
- `restoreVersion`: `console.log(\`Restoring story ${storyId} to version ${versionId} (timestamp: ${entry.timestamp})\`)`
- When retention drops entries: `console.log(\`Retention: dropped ${dropped} auto-checkpoints for story ${storyId}\`)`

No external analytics or error tracking is in scope for v1.

