| Acceptance criterion | How it is met |
|---|---|
| Auto-checkpoints every 5 minutes during active editing | `useVersionHistory` `setInterval` at 300,000ms, guarded by content-changed check |
| Auto-checkpoint fires immediately before any restore | First operation in `restoreVersion` calls `addAutoCheckpoint` |
| Named snapshots via "Save draft" button | `addNamedVersion` + input in bottom of History panel |
| Max 50 auto-checkpoints, named drafts never dropped | `enforceRetention` in `versions.ts` |
| "History" button only visible when at least one checkpoint exists | `hasVersions` guard in `page.tsx` JSX |
| History panel is a 320px right-side drawer | `.panel { width: 320px }` in CSS |
