## Risks and mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| `ViewMode` type change breaks TypeScript compilation in files that exhaustively switch on the union | The only places that consume `ViewMode` are `page.tsx` (handled in this plan), `ViewModeSwitch.tsx` (handled in this plan), and `SubmissionTracker.tsx` (which receives `viewMode` as a prop but only passes it to `ViewModeSwitch` — no switch/if on the value, so no breakage). Grep for all `ViewMode` usages before handing off to confirm no others. |
| `scenes` prop being empty array on first render causes story-order sort to map all sceneIds to `Infinity` | Acceptable for v1 — tasks will still sort stably by insertion order when all get `Infinity`. Once scenes load (they load synchronously from localStorage via `getScenes`), the sort will be correct. |
| Form inline expand causing layout shift for long task lists | The form renders as an `<li>` child inside the task list, so it pushes subsequent items down. This is acceptable UX. No animation required in v1. |
| localStorage 5 MB limit | At ~500 bytes per task, this supports 10,000+ tasks before hitting limits. Not a v1 concern. |

---

## Rollback strategy

The change is purely additive:
- `ViewMode` type gains one member. If a regression is found, remove the `'revision'` value from the union in `ViewModeSwitch.tsx` and remove the `viewMode === 'revision'` branch in `page.tsx`. All other files are new and can be deleted without affecting existing features.
- No existing localStorage keys are modified. The new key `story-{storyId}-revision-tasks` can be left in place with no side effects.

---

## Observability

All write operations in `revisionTasks.ts` should include a `console.log` call matching the pattern in `scenes.ts`:

- `addRevisionTask`: `console.log(\`Adding revision task to story ${storyId}: "${fields.title}"\`)`
- `updateRevisionTask`: `console.log(\`Updating revision task ${id} in story ${storyId}\`)`
- `deleteRevisionTask`: `console.log(\`Deleting revision task ${id} from story ${storyId}\`)`
- `completeRevisionTask`: `console.log(\`Completing revision task ${id} in story ${storyId}\`)`
- `snoozeRevisionTask`: `console.log(\`Snoozing revision task ${id} until ${new Date(until).toISOString()}\`)`

Parse errors in `getRevisionTasks` must log via `console.error('Failed to parse stored revision tasks:', error)` before returning the empty array fallback.

