## Step-by-step plan

### Phase 1: Command types (`src/types/command.ts`)

```ts
export type CommandGroup = 'recent' | 'stories' | 'scenes' | 'worldbuilding' | 'quick-actions';

export interface CommandItem {
  id: string;                 // unique string, e.g. "story-abc" or "scene-xyz"
  group: CommandGroup;
  label: string;              // primary display text
  context?: string;           // secondary text (e.g. story title for scene rows)
  modeBadge?: string;         // "Editor" | "Corkboard" optional right-side badge
  keywords?: string;          // additional search terms concatenated
  action: () => void;         // called on selection — navigation or mutation
}
```

### Phase 2: Command lib (`src/lib/commands.ts`)

**Recent items storage:**
```ts
const RECENT_KEY = 'command-palette-recent';
const RECENT_MAX = 5;

export interface RecentEntry {
  id: string;      // matches CommandItem.id
  label: string;
  context?: string;
  path: string;    // URL to navigate to on selection
  group: Exclude<CommandGroup, 'recent' | 'quick-actions'>;
}

export function getRecentEntries(): RecentEntry[]
export function pushRecentEntry(entry: RecentEntry): void   // prepend + dedup + slice(0, RECENT_MAX)
```

**Build command list:**
```ts
import { getStories } from '@/lib/stories';
import { getScenes }  from '@/lib/scenes';

export function buildCommands(
  router: { push: (url: string) => void },
  currentPath: string
): CommandItem[]
```

Implementation of `buildCommands`:
1. Pull `stories = getStories()` (non-archived first, then archived)
2. For each story, call `getScenes(story.id)` — safe because localStorage, no I/O wait
3. Build `stories` group: one CommandItem per story with `action: () => { pushRecentEntry(...); router.push('/story/' + story.id) }`
4. Build `scenes` group: one CommandItem per scene with `context = story.title`, `action: () => { pushRecentEntry(...); router.push('/story/' + story.id) }`
5. Build `worldbuilding` group: empty array for v1 — renders as "No worldbuilding data yet" in empty state
6. Build `quick-actions` group with exactly these items:
   - "New story" → navigate to `/stories`
   - "Go to Stories" → navigate to `/stories`
   - "Open Settings" → navigate to `/settings`
   - "Go to Home" → navigate to `/`
   - If `currentPath.startsWith('/story/')`: extract storyId and add:
     - "Switch to Editor" → navigate to current story URL (no-op if already editor — page handles state)
     - "Switch to Corkboard" → navigate to current story URL (page handles state)
     (v1: these are navigation hints; actual view-mode switching happens client-side in page.tsx)
7. Build `recent` group from `getRecentEntries()` with stored paths
8. Return: `[...recent, ...quickActions, ...stories, ...scenes]` — order determines display grouping

**Search filter:**
```ts
export function filterCommands(items: CommandItem[], query: string): CommandItem[]
```
- If `query.trim() === ''`: return all items (full list shown idle)
- Otherwise: case-insensitive `.includes()` match against `item.label + ' ' + (item.context ?? '') + ' ' + (item.keywords ?? '')`
- Preserve group order within results
- For 200+ scenes: O(n) string scan is fast (<5ms), no throttling needed

### Phase 3: CommandPalette component

**`CommandPalette.tsx`**

Props:
```ts
interface Props {
  isOpen: boolean;
  onClose: () => void;
  currentPath: string;
  router: { push: (url: string) => void };
}
```

Internal state:
```ts
const [query, setQuery] = useState('');
const [activeIndex, setActiveIndex] = useState(0);
const inputRef = useRef<HTMLInputElement>(null);
```

On `isOpen` change to `true`:
- `useEffect(() => { if (isOpen) { setQuery(''); setActiveIndex(0); inputRef.current?.focus(); } }, [isOpen])`

On `query` change: recompute filtered items, reset `activeIndex` to 0.

`allItems = useMemo(() => buildCommands(router, currentPath), [router, currentPath])` — rebuild on every open (fresh data)

`filteredItems = useMemo(() => filterCommands(allItems, query), [allItems, query])`

Group the filtered items for rendering:
```ts
const groups: { group: CommandGroup; label: string; items: CommandItem[] }[]
```
Group order: `['recent', 'quick-actions', 'stories', 'scenes', 'worldbuilding']`
Group display labels: `Recent`, `Quick Actions`, `Stories`, `Scenes`, `Worldbuilding`
Only render group if it has ≥1 item (except worldbuilding: render with empty state message)

Keyboard handler (`onKeyDown` on the wrapper div):
- `ArrowDown`: `setActiveIndex(i => Math.min(i + 1, filteredItems.length - 1))`
- `ArrowUp`: `setActiveIndex(i => Math.max(i - 1, 0))`
- `Enter`: call `filteredItems[activeIndex]?.action(); onClose()`
- `Escape`: `onClose()`

Focus trap: `onKeyDown` Tab → focus stays in input (prevent default)

Selection handler: `handleSelect(item: CommandItem) { item.action(); onClose(); }`

Scroll-active-into-view: `useEffect` on `activeIndex` change — `document.getElementById('cmd-item-' + activeIndex)?.scrollIntoView({ block: 'nearest' })`

JSX structure:
```tsx
{isOpen && (
  <>
    {/* Overlay */}
    <div className={styles.overlay} onClick={onClose} aria-hidden="true" />

    {/* Panel */}
    <div
      role="dialog"
      aria-modal="true"
      aria-label="Command palette"
      className={styles.panel}
      onKeyDown={handleKeyDown}
    >
      {/* Search input */}
      <div className={styles.inputRow}>
        <svg aria-hidden="true" className={styles.searchIcon}>…</svg>
        <input
          ref={inputRef}
          type="text"
          role="combobox"
          aria-expanded="true"
          aria-autocomplete="list"
          aria-controls="cmd-results"
          className={styles.input}
          placeholder="Search stories, scenes, actions…"
          value={query}
          onChange={e => { setQuery(e.target.value); setActiveIndex(0); }}
        />
        {query && (
          <button className={styles.clearButton} onClick={() => setQuery('')} aria-label="Clear search">✕</button>
        )}
      </div>

      {/* Results list */}
      <ul id="cmd-results" role="listbox" className={styles.results}>
        {/* render groups with sticky headers */}
        {groups.map(group => (
          <li key={group.group} className={styles.groupSection}>
            <div className={styles.groupHeader} aria-hidden="true">{group.label}</div>
            {group.items.length === 0 && group.group === 'worldbuilding' ? (
              <div className={styles.emptyGroup}>No worldbuilding data yet</div>
            ) : (
              group.items.map(item => {
                const flatIdx = filteredItems.indexOf(item);
                return (
                  <div
                    key={item.id}
                    id={`cmd-item-${flatIdx}`}
                    role="option"
                    aria-selected={flatIdx === activeIndex}
                    className={`${styles.resultRow} ${flatIdx === activeIndex ? styles.active : ''}`}
                    onClick={() => handleSelect(item)}
                    onMouseEnter={() => setActiveIndex(flatIdx)}
                  >
                    <span className={styles.rowLabel}>{item.label}</span>
                    {item.context && <span className={styles.rowContext}>{item.context}</span>}
                    {item.modeBadge && <span className={styles.modeBadge}>{item.modeBadge}</span>}
                  </div>
                );
              })
            )}
          </li>
        ))}
        {filteredItems.length === 0 && query && (
          <li className={styles.emptyState}>
            No matches for "<strong>{query}</strong>" — try a scene title, chapter, or character name
          </li>
        )}
      </ul>

      {/* Footer hints */}
      <div className={styles.footer} aria-hidden="true">
        <span>↑↓ navigate</span>
        <span>↵ select</span>
        <span>Esc close</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </>
)}
```

