- Focus returns to `⌘K` button on close (or editor textarea if that was focused)
- WCAG AA contrast: active row, context text, group headers

**Mobile:**
- On <768px: full-screen panel, no overlay, close button visible
- External keyboard shortcut still opens palette

## Risks and mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| `buildCommands` iterates all stories' scenes on every palette open — O(n×m) with 200+ scenes | localStorage reads are synchronous and fast; O(n) scan <5ms in practice — acceptable v1 |
| Worldbuilding entities missing | Graceful: `worldbuilding` group rendered with empty-state message; no error |
| `Cmd+K` conflicts with browser "new tab" on some locales | `e.preventDefault()` in handler prevents browser default; standard convention |
| AppShell `useRouter` addition changes server/client boundary | AppShell is already `'use client'`; `useRouter` is safe |
| Focus restoration on close | Track `lastFocusRef = useRef<Element \| null>(null)` before open, restore in onClose — add to AppShell |
| `groupSection` with `display: contents` may break sticky group headers | Use `role="group"` on a `<div>` wrapper with `display: flex; flex-direction: column` instead of `display: contents` |

**Focus restoration addition to AppShell:**
```ts
const lastFocusRef = useRef<Element | null>(null);
// before opening:
const handleOpenPalette = () => {
  lastFocusRef.current = document.activeElement;
  setIsPaletteOpen(true);
};
// in onClose:
const handleClosePalette = () => {
  setIsPaletteOpen(false);
  requestAnimationFrame(() => (lastFocusRef.current as HTMLElement)?.focus());
};
```
Pass `handleOpenPalette` to Header and `handleClosePalette` to CommandPalette.

## Rollback strategy

All additive. Remove `CommandPalette` mount from AppShell JSX to disable. Remove `onOpenPalette` prop from Header (optional prop, no-op if absent). Remove `useEffect` keyboard listener. No data migrations required.

## Observability

- No console.log in new code (maintain BIN-73 standards)
- Future: instrument `command_palette_opened`, `command_palette_selected` (group + result type) for feature adoption tracking

## Acceptance mapping

| Acceptance criterion | Covered by |
|---|---|
| Open/close entirely with keyboard | Phase 4.3 keyboard listener (`Cmd/Ctrl+K`), Phase 3 `Escape` handler |
| Search includes stories, chapters, scenes, worldbuilding | Phase 2 `buildCommands` — all four groups built |
| Selecting a result navigates in one action | Phase 3 `handleSelect` → `item.action()` → `router.push()` |
| Quick actions perform and provide immediate feedback | Phase 2 quick-actions group; navigation is immediate; future toast for mutating actions |
| Palette responsive with 200+ scenes | Phase 2 notes O(n) scan + Phase 3 `useMemo` memoization |

