### Phase 3: SyncStatusChip component

**`SyncStatusChip.tsx`**

Props: `{ storyId: string; onClick?: () => void }`

Reads status on mount and on a 30-second polling interval via `useEffect`:
```ts
const [status, setStatus] = useState<SyncStatusValue>(() => getSyncStatus(storyId));
useEffect(() => {
  const interval = setInterval(() => setStatus(getSyncStatus(storyId)), 30_000);
  return () => clearInterval(interval);
}, [storyId]);
```

Status → display text + icon:
| Status | Text | Icon (SVG inline) |
|---|---|---|
| `off` | — | hidden (render null) |
| `idle` | — | hidden (render null) |
| `syncing` | "Syncing…" | spinner SVG |
| `synced` | "Synced" | checkmark SVG |
| `conflict` | "Conflict" | warning SVG |
| `failed` | "Sync failed" | X SVG |

For `off` and `idle`: render nothing (null) — keeps headers uncluttered when sync is off.

```tsx
if (status === 'off' || status === 'idle') return null;
return (
  <button
    className={`${styles.chip} ${styles[status]}`}
    onClick={onClick}
    aria-label={`Sync status: ${statusText}. Click to manage.`}
    type="button"
  >
    <span className={styles.icon} aria-hidden="true">{icon}</span>
    <span>{statusText}</span>
  </button>
);
```

