## Risks and mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Stored scenes lack new fields | Migration in `getScenes` spreads `timelineDate: ''` and `storylineTag: ''` defaults |
| Free-text `timelineDate` sort is best-effort | Documented: ISO dates sort correctly; free-text is advisory only |
| Adding `'timeline'` to `ViewMode` breaks downstream consumers | All consumers use `ViewMode` as a union; widening is backward-compatible |
| Conflict detection O(n²) per tag | Scene counts are small (<100s); not a performance concern for v1 |

## Rollback strategy

All additive. Remove `'timeline'` from `ViewMode`, the JSX branch, and the import to disable. Delete `src/components/Timeline/` and `src/lib/timeline.ts`. Remove optional Scene fields (they're optional, stored data unaffected).

## Observability

- `updateSceneFields` already logs field updates — timeline fields appear automatically
- `detectConflicts` is a pure function, easily unit-tested in isolation
- No async operations; no new error boundaries needed

## Acceptance mapping

| Criterion | Covered by |
|---|---|
| Optional timeline metadata per scene | Step 1 `timelineDate?`/`storylineTag?`, Step 6 inline editing |
| Scenes displayed in chronological order | Step 3 `sortForTimeline`, Step 7 useMemo |
| Flag scenes without timeline data | Step 7 `noDateSceneIds` → `hasNoDate` prop → Step 6 badge |
| Detect conflicts (duplicate markers in same storyline) | Step 3 `detectConflicts`, Step 7 `conflictSceneIds` |
| Inline metadata editing | Step 6 `TimelineRow` click-to-edit inputs |
| Filter by conflicts only | Step 5 strip + Step 7 filter logic |
| Access from existing view-mode control | Step 4 `ViewModeSwitch` addition |
| Summary strip with counts/guidance | Step 5 `TimelineSummaryStrip` |

