## Step-by-step plan

### Step 1 — Define the data model (`src/types/worldbuilding.ts`)

```ts
export type EntityType = 'character' | 'location' | 'lore';

export interface WorldbuildingEntity {
  id: string;              // crypto.randomUUID()
  storyId: string;
  type: EntityType;
  name: string;            // required, max 80 chars
  notes: string;           // optional freeform text
  tags: string[];          // optional, for future filtering
  createdAt: number;
  updatedAt: number;
}

export interface SceneEntityLink {
  sceneId: string;
  entityId: string;
  linkedAt: number;
}
```

The schema is intentionally minimal. `tags` is empty-array-default for forward compatibility but not exposed in v1 UI beyond storage. `notes` replaces any rich-text body — single plain text field.

### Step 2 — Build the persistence layer (`src/lib/worldbuilding.ts`)

localStorage key conventions (matching existing patterns in `scenes.ts` and `autosave.ts`):

```
story-{storyId}-entities          → WorldbuildingEntity[]
story-{storyId}-scene-entity-links → SceneEntityLink[]
```

Implement the following pure functions (all guard `typeof window === 'undefined'`):

- `getEntities(storyId: string): WorldbuildingEntity[]` — parse, sort by `updatedAt` desc
- `getEntity(storyId: string, entityId: string): WorldbuildingEntity | null`
- `createEntity(storyId: string, data: Pick<WorldbuildingEntity, 'type' | 'name' | 'notes' | 'tags'>): WorldbuildingEntity` — assigns `id`, `storyId`, timestamps
- `updateEntity(storyId: string, entityId: string, updates: Partial<Pick<WorldbuildingEntity, 'name' | 'notes' | 'tags'>>): WorldbuildingEntity | null` — updates `updatedAt`
- `deleteEntity(storyId: string, entityId: string): void` — removes entity and all its links
- `getLinks(storyId: string): SceneEntityLink[]`
- `getLinksForScene(storyId: string, sceneId: string): SceneEntityLink[]`
- `getLinksForEntity(storyId: string, entityId: string): SceneEntityLink[]`
- `linkEntityToScene(storyId: string, entityId: string, sceneId: string): void` — idempotent (no-op if already linked)
- `unlinkEntityFromScene(storyId: string, entityId: string, sceneId: string): void`

Each write function wraps the `localStorage.setItem` call in try/catch and re-throws so the calling hook can surface errors.

### Step 3 — Build the state hook (`src/hooks/useWorldbuilding.ts`)

```ts
interface UseWorldbuildingResult {
  entities: WorldbuildingEntity[];
  links: SceneEntityLink[];
  loading: boolean;
  error: string | null;
  createEntity: (data: Pick<WorldbuildingEntity, 'type' | 'name' | 'notes' | 'tags'>) => void;
  updateEntity: (id: string, updates: Partial<Pick<WorldbuildingEntity, 'name' | 'notes' | 'tags'>>) => void;
  deleteEntity: (id: string) => void;
  linkEntity: (entityId: string, sceneId: string) => void;
  unlinkEntity: (entityId: string, sceneId: string) => void;
  retryLoad: () => void;
}

export function useWorldbuilding(storyId: string): UseWorldbuildingResult
```

Internal behavior:
- Initial load reads both `getEntities` and `getLinks` inside a try/catch; sets `loading: true` then `false`.
- Each mutation calls the lib function, re-reads the full list, updates state. Errors are caught and surfaced via `error` string; mutations clear error on next successful call.
- `retryLoad` resets `error` to null and re-runs the initial load sequence.
- No debouncing needed — writes are synchronous localStorage; state updates happen immediately.

### Step 4 — Build `PanelErrorStrip` (`src/components/WorldbuildingPanel/PanelErrorStrip.tsx`)

Small inline component. Props: `message: string`, `onRetry: () => void`. Uses `role="alert"`. Styled with `--color-fog-200` background, `--color-fashion-300` border, `--font-size-sm` text, `--spacing-sm` padding. No modal, no overlay — sits inline at top of panel body.

### Step 5 — Build `SceneSelector` (`src/components/WorldbuildingPanel/SceneSelector.tsx`)

Props:
```ts
interface SceneSelectorProps {
  scenes: Scene[];
  selectedSceneId: string | null;
  onChange: (sceneId: string) => void;
}
```

Renders a `<select>` element with `<option>` per scene (label: `scene.title`). Falls back to "No scenes yet" disabled option when `scenes` is empty. Styled as a compact `--font-size-sm` select matching the existing `statusSelect` pattern in `SceneCard.module.css` — `--color-polar-100` background, `--border-width` border, `--color-fashion-300` border color, `--border-radius-sm`.

### Step 6 — Build `EntityRow` (`src/components/WorldbuildingPanel/EntityRow.tsx`)

Props:
```ts
interface EntityRowProps {
  entity: WorldbuildingEntity;
  isLinked: boolean;
  onLinkToggle: () => void;
  onEdit: () => void;
  onDelete: () => void;
}
```

Layout: horizontal row with a link-toggle button on the left (checkbox-style, `aria-pressed={isLinked}`), entity name in the middle, and a `···` action button on the right that opens an inline dropdown (Rename / Delete). The action dropdown uses the same click-outside pattern as `StoryActionMenu`.

Linked state: when `isLinked`, the toggle button renders a filled square icon (`■`) and has `aria-label="Unlink from scene"`; when unlinked it renders an empty square (`□`) with `aria-label="Link to scene"`. Both respond to Enter/Space.

Expand/preview: clicking the entity name area opens `EntityDetailModal` in edit mode. There is no separate expand state in the row itself — the modal is the preview.

Inline success feedback: on link/unlink, briefly apply a `.justLinked` / `.justUnlinked` CSS class to the row (via a 1.2s timeout-cleared ref) that changes the border-left color from `--color-fashion-300` to `--color-carbon-600`, providing the subtle confirmation called for in the design brief without introducing toast infrastructure.

### Step 7 — Build `EntityList` (`src/components/WorldbuildingPanel/EntityList.tsx`)

Props:
```ts
interface EntityListProps {
  entities: WorldbuildingEntity[];
  linkedEntityIds: Set<string>;
  loading: boolean;
  activeType: EntityType;
  searchQuery: string;
  onLinkToggle: (entityId: string) => void;
  onEdit: (entity: WorldbuildingEntity) => void;
  onDelete: (entityId: string) => void;
}
```

Behavior:
- When `loading` is true: render 3 skeleton rows. Each skeleton row is a `div` with `--color-fog-200` background, `--border-radius-sm`, and a CSS `@keyframes` shimmer animation (opacity pulse 0.4→1→0.4 over 1.5s).
- Filter `entities` by `activeType`, then by `searchQuery` (case-insensitive match on `name` and `notes`).
- When filtered list is empty and not loading: render the empty-state message. Message text by type:
  - character: "No characters yet. Create one to start linking context."
  - location: "No locations yet. Add a place to anchor your scenes."
  - lore: "No lore yet. Capture world rules and history here."
- Otherwise render an `EntityRow` per filtered entity.

### Step 8 — Build `EntityDetailModal` (`src/components/WorldbuildingPanel/EntityDetailModal.tsx`)

Props:
```ts
interface EntityDetailModalProps {
  isOpen: boolean;
  mode: 'create' | 'edit';
  entity?: WorldbuildingEntity;       // required when mode='edit'
  defaultType?: EntityType;           // used for pre-selecting tab in create mode
  onSave: (data: Pick<WorldbuildingEntity, 'type' | 'name' | 'notes' | 'tags'>) => void;
  onDelete?: () => void;              // only in edit mode
  onClose: () => void;
}
```

Structure (mirrors `ConfirmDialog` pattern):
- Fixed overlay (`position: fixed`, `z-index: var(--z-modal)`) + centered dialog card (`max-width: 480px`, `background: var(--color-white)`, `--shadow-lg`, `--border-radius-md`).
- Header: title ("New Character" / "Edit Character" / etc.) + close button (×). Close button `aria-label="Close"`.
- Form fields:
  - Type selector: segmented button group (Character / Location / Lore). Hidden in edit mode (type cannot change after creation).
  - Name input: `<input type="text">`, `aria-label="Name"`, `maxLength={80}`, autofocused on open.
  - Notes textarea: `<textarea rows={4}>`, `aria-label="Notes"`, resizable vertically.
- Footer actions: left side shows "Delete" button (only in edit mode, styled same as `.destructiveButton` from ConfirmDialog) — clicking opens `ConfirmDialog` for delete confirmation; right side has "Cancel" and "Save" buttons.
- Keyboard: Escape closes, Enter in name field moves focus to notes. `role="dialog"`, `aria-labelledby` pointing to header title.
- Focus management: `useEffect` focuses the name input when `isOpen` flips to true (same pattern as `ConfirmDialog`).

Use the existing `ConfirmDialog` component (already in codebase) for the nested delete-confirmation within edit mode. Pass `destructive={true}`.

### Step 9 — Build `WorldbuildingPanel` (`src/components/WorldbuildingPanel/WorldbuildingPanel.tsx`)

Props:
```ts
interface WorldbuildingPanelProps {
  storyId: string;
  scenes: Scene[];
  selectedSceneId: string | null;
  onSelectedSceneChange: (sceneId: string) => void;
  isCollapsed: boolean;
  onCollapseToggle: () => void;
}
```

Internal state (all in-component, not in page.tsx — fulfilling "preserve filter/search state in-session" requirement):
- `activeType: EntityType` — default `'character'`
- `searchQuery: string` — default `''`
- `modalState: { open: boolean; mode: 'create' | 'edit'; entity?: WorldbuildingEntity; defaultType?: EntityType }` — default closed

Uses `useWorldbuilding(storyId)` hook for entity data and mutations.

Derived values:
- `linkedEntityIds: Set<string>` — built from `links.filter(l => l.sceneId === selectedSceneId).map(l => l.entityId)`
- `linkedEntities: WorldbuildingEntity[]` — entities whose IDs are in `linkedEntityIds`

Layout structure (collapsed and expanded):

**Collapsed (desktop rail, ~48px wide):**
```
[sidebar with width: 48px, overflow: hidden]
  [vertical collapse toggle button with "›" arrow, aria-label="Expand worldbuilding panel"]
```
The `editorLayout` grid changes to `1fr 48px` when collapsed.

**Expanded (~300px, default):**
```
[panel header]
  "Worldbuilding" label + collapse button ("‹")
[SceneSelector] — only shown when scenes.length > 0
[search input]  — placeholder "Search entities…", aria-label="Search worldbuilding entities"
[type tabs]     — Character | Location | Lore
[EntityList]    — filtered by type + search, with link toggles for selectedSceneId
[PanelErrorStrip] — only when error is non-null
---divider---
[linked section header] — "Linked to this scene" uppercase label
[linked entity chips]   — compact read-only chips, one per linked entity, with unlink (×) button
  [empty linked state]  — "No entities linked yet." when 0 linked
```

The "+" create button is placed in the type tabs row, right-aligned: `+ Character` (label changes with `activeType`). Clicking it opens `EntityDetailModal` in create mode with `defaultType={activeType}`.

Event wiring:
- `onLinkToggle(entityId)`: if already linked → `unlinkEntity(entityId, selectedSceneId!)`; else → `linkEntity(entityId, selectedSceneId!)`. Guard: if `selectedSceneId` is null, show `PanelErrorStrip` with message "Select a scene above to link entities."
- `onEdit(entity)`: open modal in edit mode.
- `onDelete(entityId)`: call `deleteEntity(entityId)`.
- Modal `onSave`: if create → `createEntity(data)`; if edit → `updateEntity(entity.id, data)`. Then close modal.

