## Risks and mitigations

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|---|
| `selectedSceneId` null on first load (no scenes) | Medium | Link toggle silently fails | Guard in `WorldbuildingPanel`: if `selectedSceneId` is null and user attempts to link, show `PanelErrorStrip` with actionable message. Auto-default to `scenes[0].id` via `useEffect` in page once scenes load. |
| localStorage quota exhaustion with many entities | Low | `createEntity` throws | All lib write functions throw on `localStorage.setItem` error; hook catches and surfaces via `error` string; `PanelErrorStrip` shows retry button. |
| CSS `:has()` selector for collapsed grid not supported in older browsers | Low | Grid stays at 1fr 300px when collapsed | As fallback, also apply a `sidebarCollapsed` class directly to `.editorLayout` via an inline style or a conditional `data-collapsed` attribute on the `editorLayout` div. Prefer `data-collapsed` attribute approach: `<div className={styles.editorLayout} data-sidebar-collapsed={panelCollapsed || undefined}>` with CSS selector `.editorLayout[data-sidebar-collapsed] { grid-template-columns: 1fr 48px; }`. |
| Tablet overlay backdrop — no explicit backdrop click-close | Medium | Panel cannot close on tablet | Add a click-outside handler in `WorldbuildingPanel` (same pattern as `StoryActionMenu`) that calls `onCollapseToggle()` when clicking outside the panel on tablet/mobile. |
| `deleteEntity` removing links but leaving stale React state | Medium | UI shows phantom linked entities | `useWorldbuilding` hook re-reads both `getEntities` and `getLinks` after every mutation, ensuring derived `linkedEntityIds` stays consistent. |
| Modal nested inside panel inside aside — stacking context issues | Low | Modal appears behind sidebar | `EntityDetailModal` uses `position: fixed` with `z-index: var(--z-modal)` (1300), which escapes any stacking context. |

