## Rollback strategy

All changes are additive or replace an existing placeholder. The existing sidebar `<aside>` contained only static placeholder text — restoring it requires:

1. Reverting `src/app/story/[id]/page.tsx` to remove `WorldbuildingPanel` import and the two new state variables (`selectedSceneId`, `panelCollapsed`), and restoring the original `<aside>` contents.
2. Reverting the CSS additions in `page.module.css` (removing `sidebarCollapsed`, `sidebarOpen`, and updated media queries; restoring `display: none` at tablet).
3. All new files (`src/types/worldbuilding.ts`, `src/lib/worldbuilding.ts`, `src/hooks/useWorldbuilding.ts`, `src/components/WorldbuildingPanel/`) can be left in place without causing harm — they export nothing that is imported by existing code.
4. localStorage keys (`story-{id}-entities`, `story-{id}-scene-entity-links`) are new and isolated; existing story/scene/autosave data is untouched.

