## Acceptance mapping

| Acceptance criterion | How it is met |
|---|---|
| Writer can create/edit/delete character, location, and lore entities | `EntityDetailModal` in create and edit modes; `deleteEntity` via modal footer + `ConfirmDialog` confirmation |
| Writer can link/unlink entities to a scene from the editor | Link toggle in `EntityRow`; unlink × button in linked-chips section; both guarded by `selectedSceneId` |
| Scene view shows linked entities without leaving the draft context | "Linked to this scene" section in `WorldbuildingPanel` within the existing editor sidebar; `SceneSelector` allows switching active scene without leaving editor |
| Panel can be collapsed and reopened without losing draft state | `panelCollapsed` state lives in page.tsx (survives view-mode switches within editor); `activeType`, `searchQuery`, `modalState` live inside `WorldbuildingPanel` component (survive collapse/expand within same editor session) |

